column1: 212037;instagram;2019-02-14 23:15:01;FALSE;"we confuse so many things with love and for some it becomes a serious life threatening situation but there is not enough education out there about this for us to know how truly close to death you are when someone strangles you. four minutes with only 11lbs. of pressure. a handshake is 80lbs. of pressure. your veins can collapse with 33lbs. of pressure. people really do not understand the internal injuries that happen from strangulation. your brain gets injured every time it happens. you have a greater risk of stroke because it happened. the stress hormones flooding your body damage your brain and your health. i know today there are millions of women out there putting a on brave face and going through the motions with a someone who has done this to them. i hope some of them read this and take it seriously and realize how dire it is to speak up about what happened to authorities so in the event it happens again you get the help you need to save your life.

column2: i find myself finally believing that i deserve a loving partnered relationship- not only just because i‚Äôm a human with a need for companionship
column3: but because i‚Äôm a *good* person. saying that out loud- and admitting that it‚Äôs really *really* true- seems strange
column4: but exhilarating. this is my gift to myself this valentine‚Äôs day

column1: here is a beautiful excerpt from amita‚Äôs extended #survivorloveletter : ‚Äúeverything in nature is here to teach you
column2: if you can learn to open to the lessons: the ocean is changed but not defined by an oil spill. the wind is changed but not defined by a nuclear explosion. the dog is changed but not defined by the fighting pit.

but a practice and an understanding. one day you will learn to wear your wounds instead of being led by them. your spirit will expand far past the edges of your pain. you will understand suffering as a universal human experience
column3: and power as the ability to feel joy and pleasure despite what you have endured.

column2: your wounds will disrupt the experience of time as linear. you and i will be able to use them to connect across time and space
column3: because the body (and the psyche) truly does keep the score. i will visit you many times over
column7: letting you weep in my arms ‚Äì i will grow up to understand how to love you in all the ways you always needed and never received.

column1: one day i will look at old photos of you: skinny brown girl with the big head and bigger glasses
column5: gender too mixed ‚Äì and marvel that what once looked ugly and spoiled looks only precious and tender and beautiful.

column1: i will always be with you
column2: just as you will always be with me
column3: until each memory is felt and released

column3: i understand the struggle of feeling guilty. i hope that you also see and understand that you are a precious being

column11: we can overcome. i invite you to give the gift of life to yourself and liberate yourself from those chains that keeps us sick in our minds

column4: because i need to confront it

column6: seeing no point of studying the test for tomorrow. it's a constant fucking cycle and i keep circling around and around. and then i come back to myself

column1: 212544;instagram;2019-02-15 12:47:37;TRUE;;"reposted from @flygurl96 -  today in black sistory we honor the silence:
we the silent screams of our foremothers
the screams tucked into the darkest places
so as not to wake the children
and see more horror in their eyes
so as not to wake the men
and see the pain of not being able to protect us
we the words that didn‚Äôt part from our teeth
we did best to know our place
we did best not to be uppity
or think that we may deserve dignity
we that learned a down cast eye
we the tears flowing like waterfalls
our feet bleed beneath our skin
our tongue tattooed with perpetual bite
we learned to suffer in silence to save ourselves
to save our men and children
with the screams of our ancestors at our backs
vengeance that has laid waiting for too long
and you will never hear the same again
our screams will echo in your souls forever
for as long as you can
but move when you hear my army
move when you hear my battle cry
move when you feel the presence of my lineage

column1: 212952;instagram;2019-02-15 20:09:16;FALSE;"according to the national sexual violence resource center * 1 in 5 women and 1 in 71 men will be raped at some point in their lives.
* in the united stares 1 in 3 women and 1 in 6 men experienced some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 51.1% of female victims of rape reported being raped by an intimate partner and 40.8% by an acquaintance.
* 52.4% of male victims report being raped by an acquaintance and 15.1% by a stranger.
* 49.5% of multiracial women and over 45% of american indian/alaska native women were subjected to some form of contact sexual violence in their lifetime.
* 91% of victims of rape and sexual assault are female
column2: and 9% are male * in 8 out of 10 cases of rape

column1: * 8% of rapes occur while the victim is at work.
the problem of sexual violence runs rampant
column2: and yet rape is the most under-reported crime; 63% of sexual assaults are not reported to police. of the remaining 37% that are reported less than 10% are instances of false reporting. the facts are clear
column3: and still the culture that would rather victims of sexually based crimes remain silent prevails.
